<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-12-0606 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper constructs a model used to determine population inversion andtransition temperature for vibrational and rotational excitations inthe lasing media of a carbon dioxide laser and establishes the accuracyand limits of applicability of the model. The model incorporates gaincoefficient measurements as well as the Einstein coefficients for thetransitions and is tested against a lasing mixture comprised of carbondioxide, nitrogen, and helium.</TEXT></DOC>